Create a JavaScript program that allows users to draw on an HTML5 canvas
model
```js
const canvas = document.getElementById("canvas");
const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

// Define the draw function to draw a line on the canvas
const drawLine = (x1, y1, x2, y2) => {
  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);
  ctx.lineTo(x2, y2);
  ctx.stroke();
};

// Event listener to listen for user input
canvas.addEventListener("mousedown", (e) => {
  const x = e.clientX;
  const y = e.clientY;
  drawline(x, y, e.clientX + 10, e.clientY + 10);
});

// Listen for mousemove event to draw a line as the mouse moves
canvas.addEventListener("mousemove", (e) => {
  const x = e.clientX;
  const y = e.clientY;
  drawline(x, y, x, y);
});

// Listen for mouseup event to finish the line
canvas.addEventListener("mouseup", () => {
  ctx.stroke();
});
```

This JavaScript program allows users to draw on an HTML5 canvas. The program defines a function called drawLine() to draw a line on the canvas. The program listens for mouse down, mouse move, and mouse up events to draw a line as the mouse moves.

